meta.description: Qantas Airways International First Lounge at Sydney Airport (SYD), Terminal 1 (International). Learn more about the lounge: amenities, photos, review, opening hours, location.

lounge.name: Qantas Airways International First Lounge

location.terminalDirections: Level 4, past Immigration, enter on Level 3 via escalators after Duty Free and prior to Gates 24-37.

lounge.description: Relax and unwind in the Qantas International First Lounge before your next flight. You will enjoy dedicated check-in, priority baggage handling, complimentary food and beverage, wireless internet, and the latest newspapers and magazines.

reviews.content: My fav anywhere, Pavlova is to die for.
Worth going. 3 types of champagne (perrier jouet, pommery and mumms rosé). Food is ok. Service a bit lacking, nowhere as nice as Cathay First in Hong Kong (They have Henriot rosé and service better).
Showing it’s age. Great views but overall disappointing, waited 20 minutes for a cappuccino; gave up and got it myself from the bar. Overcrowded and noisy.
Best I’ve been to in the world.
Amazing lounge with great views towards the city and the runway, good à la carte food, cocktails and four kinds of champagne. There’s also a wonderful spa. You could almost spend an entire day there.
This is easily one of the world’s best lounges, although it is starting to show its age (particularly in the furniture). Easy to look beyond these though with the amazing service!
Wow, very nice!  The bartender seemed offended when I asked about sparkling wine. He said ask the offerings were French and excellent. Lol. :). Meals, service etc all incredible. Thank you.
Great lounge with sweeping views.  Restaurant style service and menu is great with matching service to go with it. Love the design (like the inside of a plane with). Toilets with marble everywhere.
Took forever getting breakfast, had to ask two different people. Staff were unable to clear plates sufficiently.  Didn't seem first class to me.
This has to be the BEST lounge anywhere in the world. Great food, huge selection of drinks, great service and the best day spa. Qantas does a 5-star job.
Among the best lounges in the world!
This lounge deserves its reputation as one of the best first class lounges in the world. I think only the Lufthansa First Class Terminal is better. Restaurant dining, spa, enough said.
I was expecting the food to be good, but wow! It surpassed my expectations. The only bummer is that the spa closes so early (4:30pm). There must not be QF departures after that (I was on Cathay).
Very nice and big lounge. Nice food and drinks, friendly staff and perfect service. Best way to start your trip.
The staff are superb.. Attentive and available. Was there only for breakfast menu. Well prepared egg dishes. Lovely decor and views of tarmac.
The best lounge I've visited so far! The food is incredible for an airport lounge. The wine selection is very well curated. The coffees are outstanding. The spa is great! Can't speak highly enough!!
One of the best F-class lounges worldwide. The on demand made-to-order food is phenomenal and the choice is impressive. Service is professional and personalised as well.

Bigger then it's MEL sibling, this is without a doubt the BEST lounge I have ever experienced worldwide. You couldn't create a better start to your journey. Staff, design, food, beverage & Spa AMAZING!
Amazing. Best lounge I have ever been in. Food is just perfect.
Absolutely stellar lounge! Breakfast ordered was excellent, cooked fresh, immaculate presentation. Plenty of room to relax, the library is a nice touch. Quiet when I was there.
Just superb. How can it be that this quality of food, and the spa treatments, are free? Worth getting to the airport early for.
Imagine going to a Michelin star restaurant and walking out without paying the bill. That's the food quality, service and wine on offer. And then a spa which could be in the Maldives. The best.

This is the best lounge I have ever encountered. Exquisite food, great wine, and relaxed, yet attentive staff. I am rarely enthusiastic enough to review lounges, but it was exception today. Fantastic.
Hands down best lounge experience in the world. Best in class dining, architecture and interior design, not to mention the wonderful Payot spa. Not even Lufthansa can meet these standards
This is an amazing lounge with a great view. The restaurant and spa facilities are also very good.
This is an exceptional lounge, that I would say is probably the world's best. The restaurant is fantastic, the premium wines divine, and the spacious layout and great views are amazing.
This is one of the best lounges in the world. The range and quality of food/win are excellent. The wait staff are also personable, thoughtful, and efficient.
Probably the best airline lounge in the world! Truly outstanding in all aspects.
Perhaps one of the best lounges in the world. Here, you'll have the perfect view of the runway and of Sydney's skyline. The staff is brilliant and the food is so good.
This is one of the best, world-class lounge that offers choices of food and wine.
This is the best lounge I've been in, ever. The food is phenomenal, the showers are clean, and the spa is amazing.

location.terminalDirections: Near Gate 59, one level above the Departure Concourse.

Located at Level 1 Arrivals B, one level below check-in and departures. Entrance is inside the arrivals hall via Aerotel reception.
Level 3, enter via escalators after Duty Free and prior to Gates 24-37.
